The paper deals with revenue maximization in auctions, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT) and algorithmic mechanism design (cs.EC). The use of "black box" access to samples from the distribution suggests a focus on data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) for efficient computation. The paper also discusses the representation complexity of revenue-maximizing auctions, which could be related to machine learning (cs.AI) and computational learning theory (cs.LG).
